BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cNNSX6tykBqzjqYqw-y91
SUMMARY:Working Together to Protect and Transfer Assets - VIRTUAL WEBINAR
DTSTAMP:20260307T065923Z
DTSTART:20260318T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Description    ️ Working Together to Protect and Transfer Assets
	 Presented by: Peggy Haslach & Patrice Kreider-Hughes Location: GSBA Offic
	e Date & Time: March 18 11am - 12:30pm Join GSBA for an informative sessio
	n designed to help LGBTQ\\+ individuals\, couples\, and families protect w
	hat matters most. Working Together to Protect and Transfer Assets brings t
	ogether a financial planner and an estate planning attorney to show how co
	llaboration ensures your wishes are honored\, your assets are protected\, 
	and your loved ones are cared for. What You'll Learn How to build a truste
	d planning team that understands LGBTQ\\+ financial and legal needs Strate
	gies to protect assets during your lifetime with coordinated insurance\, i
	nvestments\, and legal planning Essential documents: durable powers of att
	orney\, healthcare directives\, wills\, and trusts Aligning beneficiary de
	signations with legal structures for seamless asset transfer Best practice
	s across diverse family structures and varying state laws Featured Speaker
	s   Peggy Haslach\, CFP\, CLU Financial Planner working with women profess
	ionals and small business owners Peggy built her practice serving women pr
	ofessionals \\(including veterinarians\, doctors\, and attorneys\\) and sm
	all business owners. After seeing first-hand how life events impact women'
	s financial security\, she pivoted careers at 53-focused on collaborative\
	, educational planning for women and LGBTQ\\+ clients. Her clients are for
	ward-thinking women who've put the pieces together-business\, life\, goals
	\, beliefs\, and savings-but want a cohesive plan they fully understand. O
	utside of work\, Peggy competes nationally in dog agility and shares that 
	passion with her wife\, Desiree\, a national and world champion handler an
	d trainer. They live in Sumner\, Washington with their three Border Collie
	s-Vista\, Cru\, and Peak.   Patrice M. Kreider-Hughes\, Esq. Founder & Pri
	ncipal\, Kreider Hughes Law\, PLLC Patrice is an estate planning and small
	-business attorney with 15\\+ years of experience. She earned her B.A. in 
	psychology from the University of Virginia and her J.D. from Seattle Unive
	rsity School of Law. Before founding Kreider Hughes Law in 2017\, she serv
	ed as in-house counsel for Conover Insurance\, handling mergers and acquis
	itions\, contracts\, and employment matters. Featured on the Seattle Conne
	cted podcast and recognized by Expertise.com in 2023 and 2024\, Patrice li
	ves in Seattle with her wife\, their daughter Simone\, and pets Luther and
	 Emma. Session Outline Why Collaboration Matters Financial planners and es
	tate attorneys working in tandem to build resilient\, values-aligned plans
	. Building Your Planning Team Roles\, responsibilities\, and coordination 
	between advisors who understand LGBTQ\\+ needs. Protecting Assets During Y
	our Lifetime Insurance \\(life\, disability\, long-term care\\)\, investme
	nt strategy \\(diversification\, ESG\\)\, and ownership/titling alignment.
	 Legal Documents That Safeguard Your Wishes Durable POA\, healthcare POA &
	 advance directive\, wills & trusts\, and syncing beneficiary designations
	. Coordinating Asset Transfers Real estate titling\, retirement & insuranc
	e beneficiaries\, business succession\, and philanthropic giving. Navigati
	ng Legal Landscapes & Family Structures Marriage recognition\, parental ri
	ghts\, cross-border/visa considerations\, and state-by-state variability. 
	Q&A \\(15 min\\) - Bring your questions on real estate\, trusts\, chosen f
	amily\, and children's inheritance planning. Who Should Attend LGBTQ\\+ in
	dividuals\, couples\, and families seeking long-term financial security Sm
	all business owners planning for succession and legacy Anyone looking to a
	lign legal and financial strategies\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events
	/#/details/working-together-to-protect-and-transfer-assets-virtual-webinar
	/18089679/2026-03-18T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Learning & Education
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/working-together-to-prote
	ct-and-transfer-assets-virtual-webinar/18089679/2026-03-18T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-learning
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Learning & Education
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT1H30M
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Umj2fKOiTMnEO8mNbRnt3
SUMMARY:Boren Banner Series: Camille Trautman
DTSTAMP:20260307T065923Z
DTSTART:20260318T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Every photograph is a reminder that the act of framing is never
	 neutral. In Camille Trautman’s first solo museum exhibition in their home
	town\, the Seattle-born Duwamish artist uses photography and video to chal
	lenge colonial narratives and counter Indigenous erasure. The exhibition p
	resents selections from their ongoing series The North American LCD—spectr
	al self-portraits staged in varied natural landscapes. Rooted in Trautman’
	s process of coming out as transgender\, the images show the artist’s body
	 partially obscured by large LCD screens. The series examines how both lan
	dscape photography and digital media can shape or distort cultural identit
	y\, often by promoting or denying visibility.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camille-trautman/16813305/2026-03
	-18T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/boren-banner-series-camil
	le-trautman/16813305/2026-03-18T00
LOCATION:Frye Art Museum\, 704 Terry Ave\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT6H
END:VEVENT
